BACKPORT PROPOSALS:

  * Allow both a C and python module to create a metric that will spoof a
    specific host.  This provides the same spoofing functionality as gmetric
    but through a metric module.  It is done by adding SPOOF_HOST and
    SPOOF_NAME as extra metadata to the metric description
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1386
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1389
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1622
    +1: bnicholes
    carenas: apparently includes few other unrelated changes

  * web: performance/security improvement for handling authorization
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1588
    +1: carenas
    +0: hawson
    -1: bernardli
    bernardli: PHP would look in the current directory for the file to include,
               therefore, adding the "./" is redundant.  In fact I would propose
               that we get rid of all the "./" for the other include_once()
               calls in web/*.
    hawson: If security is an issue, then check/set the include path with 
            the get_include_path() and set_include_path() functions.  I don't
            see that this would affect performance much.

  * gmond: mod_python support for versions older than 2.3 or newer than 2.4
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1593
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1596
    +1: carenas
    +1: bnicholes
    carenas: depends on spoofing support

  * build: libmetrics dependency cleanup
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1597
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1602
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1612
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1614
    +1: carenas
    carenas: prerequisite for mingw32 support, RPC/ON is used in core only

  * build: remove sideffects of --disable-python for dist target
    http://www.mail-archive.com/ganglia-developers@lists.sourceforge.net/msg04551.html
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1610
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1877
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1880
    +1: carenas
    -1: bnicholes
    bnicholes: There seems to be several problems with this patch. First the
      configure fails because the example directory was not included in the
      DIST_SUBDIRS and therefore none of the example source or make files are
      included in the final tarball. Second, since the .pyc are not being
      generated, the spec file fails when it tries to copy the missing .pyc 
      files.
    bnicholes: Patch r1877 fixed the first issue with the inclusion of the 
      example source, but the second issue still remains.

  * python_modules: remove unconditional debugging information for multidisk
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1623
    +1: carenas
    carenas: suboptimal fix, python framework for debug messages to wrap it

